Expand $(2z^2 + 5z - 6)(3z^3 - 2z + 1)$.
inference:
First, multiply the first term of the first polynomial by each term of the second polynomial.
$$(2z^2)(3z^3)=6z^5$$
$$(2z^2)(-2z)=-4z^3$$
$$(2z^2)(1)=2z^2$$

Next, multiply the second term of the first polynomial by each term of the second polynomial.

$$(5z)(3z^3)=15z^4$$
$$(5z)(-2z)=-10z^2$$
$$(5z)(1)=5z$$

Finally, multiply the third term of the first polynomial by each term of the second polynomial.

$$(-6)(3z^3)=-18z^3$$
$$(-6)(-2z)=12z$$
$$(-6)(1)=-6$$

Now, add the like terms together:
$$6z^5+15z^4-18z^3-4z^3-10z^2+2z^2+5z+12z-6$$
Final Answer: $\boxed{6z^5+15z^4-22z^3-8z^2+17z-6}$. I hope it is correct.
